---
description: Deno + Pylon GraphQL API conventions for apps/timemanager-api (Kysely + Postgres).
globs: apps/timemanager-api/**
---

`apps/timemanager-api` is a **Deno** app (Pylon GraphQL) — use `deno.json` tasks, NOT Node, Bun, npm, or pnpm here. Dependencies are declared in `deno.json` `imports`.

Stack: [Pylon](https://pylon.cronit.io/) (`@getcronit/pylon`) for GraphQL, [Kysely](https://kysely.dev/) query builder over Postgres (`pg`). Serves on `:3000`.

Source layout (`src/`):

- `index.ts` — entrypoint.
- `graphql/` — `schema.ts`, `types.ts`, `resolvers/resolvers.ts`.
- `db/` — `database.ts` (Kysely + pg pool), `types/schema.ts` (DB types), `migrations/` (timestamped `*.ts` + `migration.ts` runner), `seed.ts`.

Commands (via `deno task`, or the Nx wrappers `nx serve|build|run timemanager-api`):

- `deno task dev` — dev server (Nx `serve`, which also runs `timemanager-db:up`).
- `deno task build` — build.
- `deno task seed` — seed the DB (`nx run timemanager-api:seed`).

The database comes from `infra/timemanager-db` (Postgres `:5432`). Bring it up with `pnpm db:up` before running against real data.
